         <abstract>
            <p>Recently, it has been proved that a Fourier transform for the symmetric group S&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt; based on Young's seminormal form can be evaluated in less than 0.5(n&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; + n&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)n! arithmetic operations. We look at this algorithm in more detail and show that it allows an efficient software implementation using appropriate data structures. We also describe a similarly efficient algorithm for the inverse Fourier transform. We compare the time and memory requirements of our program to those of other existing implementations.</p>
          </abstract>
